01:29:04,022 --> 01:29:05,114
[CHARISSE LAUGHS]

996
01:29:05,289 --> 01:29:06,551
[CHARISSE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

997
01:29:09,794 --> 01:29:11,091
GOMEZ: You need anything?
- No.

998
01:29:11,262 --> 01:29:12,593
- Oh, I'm good, hon.
- Okay.

999
01:29:12,764 --> 01:29:14,129
HENRY: Hey, Gomez.
- Hey.

1000
01:29:14,298 --> 01:29:15,560
HENRY:
Come outside for a minute.

1001
01:29:15,733 --> 01:29:16,757
[KENDRICK SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1002
01:29:16,934 --> 01:29:18,902
- It's cold out there.
- Don't be an old man.

1003
01:29:19,070 --> 01:29:20,367
Come on, just take a second.

1004
01:29:20,538 --> 01:29:24,440
KENDRICK: Well, I've never considered
myself a performer, but I'd like to try.

1005
01:29:31,616 --> 01:29:33,516
What, uh...?

1006
01:29:33,918 --> 01:29:35,442
What's up?

1007
01:29:39,557 --> 01:29:42,025
Just wanted to say
thanks for everything, man.

1008
01:29:42,593 --> 01:29:45,528
- You've been a great friend.
- What are you talking about?

1009
01:29:47,698 --> 01:29:50,189
Something might happen tonight.

1010
01:29:50,935 --> 01:29:52,527
All right?

1011
01:29:52,703 --> 01:29:54,933
And I just wanna let you know...

1012
01:29:55,740 --> 01:29:59,198
...that I know I've been a pain in the ass,
but you've been great.

1013
01:30:00,311 --> 01:30:02,404
It's all been great.

1014
01:30:05,817 --> 01:30:09,116
Yeah. Don't mention it.

1015
01:30:10,121 --> 01:30:12,055
You guys crazy?

1016
01:30:12,924 --> 01:30:15,324
It's freezing. Baby, put this on.

1017
01:30:15,493 --> 01:30:18,053
Gomez, just give us a minute, man.

1018
01:30:30,408 --> 01:30:33,104
ALBA:
Guys, can you believe it?

1019
01:30:37,515 --> 01:30:40,416
GOMEZ:
We're gonna give them a minute or two.

1020
01:30:44,722 --> 01:30:46,622
Henry?

1021
01:30:51,229 --> 01:30:52,719
No.

1022
01:30:56,067 --> 01:30:57,432
No.

1023
01:30:58,369 --> 01:30:59,836
Come here.

1024
01:31:02,640 --> 01:31:03,902
Come on.

1025
01:31:34,138 --> 01:31:37,266
Why did you let me invite
all these people?

1026
01:31:38,676 --> 01:31:41,144
I didn't want you to be alone.

1027
01:31:50,888 --> 01:31:53,288
Hey. Hey.

1028
01:31:56,127 --> 01:31:58,493
I wouldn't change anything.

1029
01:32:00,731 --> 01:32:02,790
I would not give up...

1030
01:32:03,267 --> 01:32:06,794
...one second of our life together.

1031
01:32:25,623 --> 01:32:27,614
[FIREWORKS EXPLODE]

1032
01:32:46,177 --> 01:32:48,168
[PANTING]

1033
01:32:48,546 --> 01:32:49,877
[DEER SNORTS]

1034
01:32:55,319 --> 01:32:57,344
MAN: Got it?
PHILIP: Yeah. Shh, shh.

1035
01:32:58,189 --> 01:32:59,656
ALBA:
Dad. Dad.

1036
01:32:59,824 --> 01:33:01,257
[GRUNTS]

1037
01:33:11,902 --> 01:33:13,529
I knew I clipped it.

1038
01:33:13,704 --> 01:33:16,195
MAN: I don't see any tracks.
- Yeah.

1039
01:33:17,508 --> 01:33:18,907
Let's try over here.

1040
01:33:33,190 --> 01:33:34,714
CHARISSE:
Clare.

1041
01:33:35,326 --> 01:33:37,954
- Clare.
KENDRICK: I'm calling the hospital.

1042
01:33:38,129 --> 01:33:39,858
Okay.

1043
01:33:41,766 --> 01:33:45,497
I love you. More than anything.

1044
01:33:45,670 --> 01:33:49,470
I love you. I'll always love you. Always.

1045
01:33:49,640 --> 01:33:51,267
Stay here.

1046
01:33:58,816 --> 01:34:00,408
HENRY:
Alba, sweetie.

1047
01:34:00,584 --> 01:34:02,381
Daddy.

1048
01:34:04,088 --> 01:34:06,386
Oh, Henry.

1049
01:34:08,759 --> 01:34:10,522
Henry.

1050
01:34:12,196 --> 01:34:14,255
Sweetheart.

1051
01:34:20,471 --> 01:34:22,462
[CLARE WHIMPERING]

1052
01:35:33,043 --> 01:35:35,341
MAX:
Aah! Whoa.

1053
01:35:43,087 --> 01:35:45,715
- Daddy?
- Alba.

1054
01:35:46,857 --> 01:35:49,883
Daddy, I knew I'd see you again.
I knew it.

1055
01:35:57,501 --> 01:35:59,696
- How old are you? When is this?
- I'm 9.

1056
01:35:59,870 --> 01:36:02,896
You're 9?
And your mom still leaves clothes?

1057
01:36:03,073 --> 01:36:05,405
She says you never know.

1058
01:36:05,576 --> 01:36:09,535
You remember Max and Rosa, don't you?
Gomez's kids.

1059
01:36:09,713 --> 01:36:10,907
HENRY:
They're so grown-up.

1060
01:36:12,316 --> 01:36:16,912
Run back to the house, you guys.
Tell Mom he's here. Tell her to come.

1061
01:36:17,087 --> 01:36:18,247
Let's go.

1062
01:36:18,422 --> 01:36:19,548
ROSA:
Wait up.

1063
01:36:20,991 --> 01:36:24,324
Tell me the story
of how you and Mama met.

1064
01:36:24,495 --> 01:36:28,591
- Doesn't she tell you?
- She does, but not like you do.

1065
01:36:28,866 --> 01:36:31,460
Well, it was right here in this meadow.

1066
01:36:33,070 --> 01:36:35,368
And one fine day...

1067
01:36:35,773 --> 01:36:38,207
...your mom,
who's just a tiny little thing...

1068
01:36:38,943 --> 01:36:41,935
...goes out to the clearing,
and there's a man there.

1069
01:36:42,112 --> 01:36:45,411
- With no clothes.
- Not a stitch on him.

1070
01:36:45,583 --> 01:36:48,279
After she gives him a blanket
she happens to be carrying...

1071
01:36:48,452 --> 01:36:52,479
...he explains to her
that he's a time traveler.

1072
01:36:52,656 --> 01:36:56,820
Now, for some reason
I'll never understand...

1073
01:36:57,661 --> 01:36:58,753
...she believes him.

1074
01:36:58,929 --> 01:37:00,089
Because it's true.

1075
01:37:02,399 --> 01:37:03,491
Henry?

1076
01:37:07,037 --> 01:37:08,971
- I'm going.
- No, Daddy. Sing.

1077
01:37:09,440 --> 01:37:11,408
I can't sing.

1078
01:37:27,591 --> 01:37:28,649
Henry.

1079
01:37:28,826 --> 01:37:30,817
[LAUGHS]

1080
01:37:34,865 --> 01:37:37,129
- Where are you from?
- I'm 39.

1081
01:37:37,535 --> 01:37:40,368
Alba's just a baby.
We're in the house. We're happy.

1082
01:37:41,105 --> 01:37:44,302
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?
I would've been here waiting.

1083
01:37:44,475 --> 01:37:46,136
I didn't want you to wait.

1084
01:37:48,512 --> 01:37:50,673
I don't want you
to spend your life waiting.

1085
01:37:50,848 --> 01:37:52,179
Hmm...

1086
01:37:52,950 --> 01:37:54,577
I love you.

1087
01:37:57,321 --> 01:37:58,515
I can't stay.

1088
01:37:59,490 --> 01:38:01,219
I know.

1089
01:38:59,149 --> 01:39:00,946
ALBA:
Sometimes I think he's in the trees...

1090
01:39:01,118 --> 01:39:03,552
...deciding when to come out
and surprise me.

1091
01:39:03,721 --> 01:39:06,315
CLARE: I used to think that
when I was a little girl.

1092
01:39:06,490 --> 01:39:09,323
That he was always here,
even when he wasn't.

1093
01:39:09,493 --> 01:39:12,223
ALBA:
I guess he is, isn't he?

1094
01:47:22,003 --> 01:47:23,574
<i>{{{ the end }}} </i>
